metadata.title: Multichannel Seismic-Reflection Data North Bering Sea - Gulf of Anadyr

creators.name: Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Environmental Satellite, Data
Information Service (NESDIS), National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC)

metadata.description:
Approximately 1,800 line km of 24-channel seismic-reflection data
are now available in the Gulf of Anadyr and across the Navarin
Basin.  The data were collected during 1980 from the U.S.
Geological Survey (USGS) Research Ship (S.P. LEE using a sound
source of 5 airguns totaling 1,325 cubic inches.*
